{"source_hash": "f3d8144a54810ffb", "candidate": {"id": "cand-024", "name": "Maya Lindstr\u00f6m", "raw_cv": "MAYA LINDSTR\u00d6M\nmaya.lindstrom@email.com | London, UK\n\nSTAFF ENGINEER\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\nStaff software engineer with 11 years of experience, including 4 years at Google. Deep expertise in distributed systems, API design, and large-scale service reliability. Track record of driving technical direction across multi-team engineering organisations.\n\nEXPERIENCE\n\nStaff Engineer \u2014 Wise, London (2021\u2013present)\n- Technical lead across the FX pricing and rate distribution domain (6 teams, 40+ engineers)\n- Designed the real-time rate broadcasting system handling 50M+ rate updates/day with <10ms p99 latency\n- Defined and enforced API design standards adopted company-wide\n- Led a cross-team working group on consistency and idempotency patterns across payment flows\n- IC calibration committee member\n\nSenior Software Engineer \u2192 Staff Engineer \u2014 Google, London (2017\u20132021)\n- Worked on Google Pay backend infrastructure (Java, C++, Spanner)\n- Designed the merchant tokenisation service now processing 200M+ transactions/day\n- L6 promotion in 3.5 years\n\nSoftware Engineer \u2014 Skyscanner, Edinburgh (2013\u20132017)\n- Backend Python engineer on the flights search infrastructure\n\nSKILLS\nJava, Python, Go, gRPC, Protobuf, Spanner, PostgreSQL, Kafka, Pub/Sub, Kubernetes, distributed systems design, API design, technical leadership\n\nEDUCATION\nMEng Computer Science \u2014 University of Edinburgh (2009\u20132013)\nFirst Class Honours\n\nRIGHT TO WORK\nSwedish citizen, UK Settled Status (ILR)", "raw_linkedin": "Staff engineer at Wise, working across the FX pricing domain. Previously at Google for four years on Google Pay infrastructure. I spend most of my time now on technical strategy rather than individual features \u2014 defining architecture, unblocking teams, and making sure we don't build the same thing six different ways. I'm particularly interested in distributed systems problems around consistency, latency, and API design at scale. Swedish, UK settled status, based in London. Not actively looking but open to conversations about principal or distinguished engineer roles at ambitious companies.", "raw_interview_transcript": "Interviewer: Maya, thanks for coming in. Can you tell me about the rate broadcasting system at Wise?\n\nMaya: FX rates change constantly and Wise needs to show accurate rates to tens of millions of users across web, mobile, and partner APIs simultaneously. When I joined, the rate fan-out was synchronous and sequential \u2014 fine at low volume but completely unfit for the scale we were hitting. I designed a pub/sub based system with differential broadcasting: instead of sending full rate tables, we only broadcast deltas, and we use client-side reconciliation to detect missed updates and re-request. That got us from 10-second staleness to under 100ms for 99% of subscribers.\n\nInterviewer: How do you operate as a staff engineer day-to-day?\n\nMaya: I think of my job as multiplying the impact of the engineers around me. Concretely that means: being available for design reviews, writing the hard design docs that clarify the hairy problems, setting standards that prevent teams from making the same expensive mistakes, and occasionally doing the hands-on investigation when nobody else has the context to. I still write production code \u2014 probably 20\u201330% of my time \u2014 because I think it's important to stay grounded in the actual constraints.\n\nInterviewer: What would bring you to leave Wise at this point?\n\nMaya: The work at Wise is interesting but I'm increasingly being pulled into management territory which isn't where I want to go. I want to stay technical. The right move for me is somewhere where the IC track has real senior depth \u2014 principal, distinguished \u2014 and where there are genuinely hard technical problems to work on.\n\nInterviewer: Salary?\n\nMaya: I'm at \u00a3175,000 base at Wise. I'd need to be in that range.", "years_experience": 11.0, "skills": ["Java", "Python", "Go", "gRPC", "Protobuf", "Spanner", "PostgreSQL", "Kafka", "Pub/Sub", "Kubernetes", "distributed systems design", "API design", "technical leadership"], "industries": ["fintech", "payments", "SaaS", "cloud infrastructure"], "seniority_level": "staff", "management_experience": false, "education_level": "master", "career_trajectory": "ascending", "interview_score": 0.88, "culture_fit_score": 0.78, "constraints": [{"id": "af09b8f8", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Minimum salary expectation \u00a3175,000 (current base at Wise)", "canonical_key": "salary_min", "value": 175000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.98, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "cf0fea4d", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "career", "description": "Seeking principal or distinguished engineer level roles at ambitious companies", "canonical_key": null, "value": "principal or distinguished engineer roles", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 0.95, "confidence": 0.95, "currency": null}, {"id": "d262cc9d", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "career", "description": "Must remain on technical IC track; explicitly does not want to move into management", "canonical_key": null, "value": "technical individual contributor track", "operator": "requires", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.96, "currency": null}, {"id": "b51b0d66", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "technical", "description": "Preference for roles involving genuinely challenging technical problems, particularly distributed systems, consistency, latency, and scale", "canonical_key": null, "value": "genuinely hard technical problems", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 0.9, "confidence": 0.92, "currency": null}, {"id": "df13cf58", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "career", "description": "Seeking companies with real senior depth on the IC track (principal, distinguished engineer levels)", "canonical_key": null, "value": "senior technical depth in IC track", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 0.9, "confidence": 0.93, "currency": null}, {"id": "c4a6ac08", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "visa", "description": "Has Swedish citizenship with UK Settled Status (ILR); visa sponsorship not required", "canonical_key": "visa_sponsorship", "value": false, "operator": "excludes", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.98, "currency": null}, {"id": "e9cd7dcf", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "location", "description": "Currently based in London; no explicit relocation constraint but location shows London preference", "canonical_key": "location_city", "value": "London", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 0.7, "confidence": 0.75, "currency": null}]}, "embedding": [-0.009246826171875, 0.019195556640625, 0.092041015625, -0.0106201171875, -0.0107421875, -0.0021533966064453125, 0.005096435546875, 0.0282135009765625, -0.0269012451171875, -0.0004968643188476562, 0.0084991455078125, -0.029327392578125, -0.0167083740234375, 0.0205078125, 0.0643310546875, 0.06732177734375, -0.043731689453125, -0.0209808349609375, -0.0196380615234375, 0.038818359375, -0.0135040283203125, 0.0244293212890625, -0.0080718994140625, 0.048248291015625, 0.04180908203125, -0.01081085205078125, -0.04803466796875, 0.035064697265625, -0.0181121826171875, -0.0203704833984375, 0.06597900390625, -0.0178680419921875, -0.0219573974609375, 0.0361328125, 0.023284912109375, -0.03118896484375, 0.0172882080078125, 0.0643310546875, 0.0283660888671875, -0.030242919921875, -0.04742431640625, -0.02105712890625, -0.0089569091796875, 0.0006709098815917969, 0.01971435546875, -0.0007786750793457031, -0.0160675048828125, 0.0667724609375, 0.0250244140625, 0.04412841796875, -0.0357666015625, -0.03955078125, 0.0016574859619140625, 0.048492431640625, -0.0144195556640625, -0.01105499267578125, 0.049652099609375, 0.02880